System THE eThekwini Municipality has received information about a scam that is currently targeting pensioners with regard to completing forms for rebates on electricity consumption increases. The municipality confirms that no additional forms are required to be completed, apart from the annual renewal rebate applications and new application forms. Customers are urged to be vigilant to avoid falling prey to criminals posing as municipal employees. Any representative of the municipality will have an ID tag with a photograph, ID or employee number with the municipal logo. If residents are suspicious of anything, they can contact Revline at revline@revcall.co.za or the Revenue Call Centre on 031 324 5000. - Supplied 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  